cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a learning procedure for detection models to learn motion features directly from RGB video data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deformable convolutions, which are commonly used in deep learning models (cs.LG). The paper involves training a neural network to optimize a pose estimation task, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions spatiotemporal action localization and fine-grained action recognition, which are tasks commonly associated with multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
